articles.author: Brenda Goodman
articles.title: The Covid-19 pandemic killed off one strain of the flu, and that will change the next vaccines - CNN
articles.description: For ten years, Americans have had access to flu shots that protect against four different strains of the flu—two A strains and two B strains.
articles.content:
For 10 years, Americans have had access to flu shots that protect against four strains of the virus: two A strains and two B strains.
